Key Features
Visual Design:
EMS Switch: Custom toggle with radial gradient that transforms from gray to crimson when active
Sharingan Icon Animation: Rotating tomoe when auto-translate is enabled
Active Glow: Each toggle has its own color theme (crimson, gold, purple) with matching shadows
Ripple Effects: Click feedback with expanding circles
Functionality:
Dependency Management: OCR must be enabled before auto-translate/bubble overlay
Permission Handling: Desktop capture requests browser permissions dynamically
Batch Operations: Enable/disable all (except experimental features)
State Persistence: Automatic save/load via Chrome storage API
Master Toggle Logic: Disabling OCR auto-disables dependent features
States:
Active: Crimson gradient, spinning icons, left border accent
Disabled: Grayed out, reduced opacity, no pointer events
Experimental: "BETA" badge in corner (desktop capture)
Premium: Gold "PRO" badge (sound effects)
Events:
togglechange - Individual toggle change
batchtoggle - Mass enable/disable
Background script messaging for real-time sync
Usage in popup.html:

<quick-toggles id="mainToggles"></quick-toggles>
<script>
  document.getElementById('mainToggles').addEventListener('togglechange', (e) => {
    console.log('Toggle changed:', e.detail);
  });
</script>